Java Version 8

Project Contents:
1. MergeSort
2. InsertionSort
3. BubbleSort
4. HeapSort
5. QuickSort
6. ExecutionTime.java(Caculates execution time for each sorting method)
7. Graph_Time_Vs_Input.py(Plot graph for time complexity versus input size)

Sorting methods implemented under this project:
-----------------------------------------------------

1. MergeSort
2. InsertionSort
3. BubbleSort
4. HeapSort
5. QuickSort

Steps for code execution:
----------------------------

Step1: Import Project Source code in Eclipse

Step2: Each Sorting Method to be executed separately.
	(Separate java files for each sort)

Step3: Eclipse Output Console User input
       Below is Example for MergeSort Code:  
************************************************
Enter the Size of the array:
5

Enter the elements of the array:
16
5
8
90
4

Provided Array
[16, 5, 8, 90, 4]

Array after Sorting
[4, 5, 8, 16, 90]
************************************************

Step4: Execution time versus input size for each sorting method is implemented under 'ExecutionTime.java' and 'Graph_Time_Vs_Input.py'.(Open .py Code in Pycharm or Anaconda)
